slackbuilds that use git. There will only be 2 files per build. package.README and package.SlackBuild
all package must pass sbopkglint

Python packages uses git to download and they must all be set to specific commit.
I have used tags now but they are not that safe because they can be changed but
shasum cant, only removed. When there is a lot of git repositories we should not just
trust all of them. We look at the tarballs and diff, we look at other distribution patches
I find useful. Creating a custom Python3 in /opt/ for some apps specifically. It's a work
in progress mainly just to use the newest kitty cus I needed some functionality.
